WELCOME TO SEASON TWO! Raghunath Cappo - @RAGHUNATHYOGI -  is a masterful yoga teacher, Bhakti yoga devotee, ex-monk, punk rock icon, and a father of five. He lives in upstate New York on his SuperSoul farm, where he hosts teacher trainings and seva immersions.

In his early 20s Raghunath walked away from this life and headed to India on a spiritual pilgrimage that ultimately led him to the holy village of Vrindavan. During this time he fell in love with the wisdom, insight, and traditions of Bhakti yoga. He remained there for six years living as a monk. Inevitably returning back to the US, he has since pursued a life of sharing the teachings of yoga and taking groups on incredible pilgrimages - or Yatras - within India every year. He also facilitates exceptional yoga teacher trainings annually. Raghunath co-hosts the Wisdom Of The Sages podcast, delving deep into the Bhakti Yoga teachings from the Srimad Bhagavatam.

In this episode we unravel:

- The pivotal moments along Raghunath’s journey thus far which has influenced his work today, including his flipping the script on the punk rock culture of the time.
- His experience connecting with the Christian community and the common thread between all belief systems.
- True inclusivity, what it looks like, and how we can live it.
- The beauty of diversity.
- His interest in yoga through a desire for spiritual truth.
- The challenge in transmitting the teachings of yoga to the punk rock community, which sharpened his study and spiritual thirst.
- Upper case “Love”.
- The essence of the Bhakti Yoga tradition.
- The path of Bhukti and Mukti.
- How to understand the context of the Bhagavad Gita.
- The holy vortexes of India.
- The value of being held by a teacher when venturing throughout India and holy places.
- Raghunath’s biggest takeaway and lesson from being a parent.

Connect with Raghunath at https://www.raghunath.yoga/

I’ve wanted to build a stone wall since i was a teenager growing up in Connecticut. At 57- I finally did it. Once we made the patio  with assistance from @live.to.be.corrected  I thought this is my chance. I had been saving rocks for literally 8 years. I know that may sound stupid but I had saved rocks whenever I found cool big ones in the woods -just putting them in piles around the yard using my #kubotatractor  after a few YouTube videos we started laying the foundation. 
Thanks to all the friends that helped. An incredible work out. Exhausting. Joyful. And it’s an amazing puzzle that wants to figured out. There’s something special about being with stones and almost asking them where they want to go. Stone walls are the closest things to eternality in this world.

LIGHT ON WISDOM TRAINING 
with KAUSTUBHA DAS, RAGHUNATH, DAYAL GAURANGA & special guest RADHANATH SWAMI 
Where: Govardhana Eco Village, India (2 hours outside of Mumbai)  
When: January 14, 2023 - January 26, 2024 
Price: By Donation ($1100 base price to cover base expenses, plus a donation for the teachers)

FOR MORE INFO & REGISTRATION - LINK IN BIO

If you ever wanted to have time away from the daily grind to learn yoga wisdom in-depth and have all of your questions answered in a supportive environment, this is your chance. The daily schedule will include kirtan and story telling with Raghunath in the mornings and evenings, classes with Kaustubha and Dayal Gauranga during the day, and open time for study, journaling and meditation. There will also be special talks by Radhanath Swami.
 ABOUT THE TRAINING
Two weeks in a beautiful, ashram setting, with time to explore the path of Bhakti-yoga.
 • Excellent Teachers: presenting courses going deeper into the tradition.
 • Perfect Setting: under the trees and in the temple courtyards of the beautiful Govardhan Eco Village in India.
 • Perfect Time: The weather in the region is ideal in January, and we have all day, to take the time to answer your questions and go deep.
 • Great People: Our trainings at the Eco Village always attracts a group of sincere people with bonds of friendship being made.
 • Great Mood: Kind, open and fun!

Govardhan EcoVillage, a spiritual oasis that illustrates the principles of ‘Simple Living and High Thinking', is situated amidst the lush green Sahyadri mountain ranges in Wada district, just a two-hour drive from Mumbai, and is equipped with an authentic yoga school, eco-stay rooms, a Kerala Ayurveda Center, beautiful shelters for our cows, a sound room, and many more amenities ensuring a comfortable stay.

Humbled to be recognized by the World Tourism Organization (UNWTO) for promoting sustainable tourism, Govardhan EcoVillage is a perfect place to find inner peace.

Govardhan EcoVillage serves students from all over the world as a temple of learning for spirituality, yoga, ayurveda, sustainability, vedic sciences, and performing arts and strives to preserve, promote, and share this rich cultural heritage of India.

Last day in 🇮🇳India. Biked around old Delhi. 
Love this place that you can:

- ride domestic planes barefoot
-say Jaya Shri Rama to most everyone and watch them become completely animated and excited and want to talk to you. 
-bust out loud Kirtan’s in hotel lobbies,rest stops, and most public places. Instead of complaints people will all join in. 
-get the most respect for having nothing 
- you can get a giant thali for dinner for under $3.50
- ride 5 on Scooter
- straight men show  affection to one another by holding hands regularly walking down the street 
-food is freshly made. 
- sweets are works of art…
-eat roadside food that is incredible (this morning kachoris, hulva,pooris,aloo subji & jalebi)
-lay down and take a nap anywhere. People do it. Even the wealthy. Just lay down. 
-see old ladies with OM tattoos on their hands. 

What did I miss?
